under ADB TA 3413-LAO: Rural Finance Development indicates 
that it needs to be replaced. This was confirmed by an ICT Strategy 
for the Lao Banking Sector prepared by the Bank of Lao PDR (BOL, 
the central bank) with the assistance of the European Union (EU). 

While the purchase of the hardware and software for the new system 
will be financed by an ADB loan (see Financing Plan below and 
Costs in appendix), this Component will assist APB staff to carry out 
the following highly technical activities, which are currently beyond 
APB’s capacity:  

•  review and confirm that the systems specifications proposed 
are adequate for APB’s needs; 
•  plan  and  execute  the  bidding,  selection  and  contracting 
processes with the turnkey contractor and the communication 
infrastructure provider; 
•  monitor  the  turnkey  installation  and  milestone  achievement, 
verify that specifications have been adhered to, review data 
migration plans, and carry out user acceptance testing;  
•  review  and  evaluate  the  effectiveness  of  technical  and 
operational training provided under the turnkey contract; and 
•  plan and implement the rollout of systems to the whole APB 
branch network. 
Monitorable Deliverables/Outputs  •  Finalized user requirements;  
•  Finalized technical specifications;  
•  Finalized turnkey bidding documents;  
•  Prequalified bidders;  
•  Evaluated bids;  
•  Signed turnkey contract;  
•  Signed communications contract;  
•  Turnkey  contract  oversight  reports  from  supervision 
consultants;  
•  Signed off user acceptance testing report;  
•  Signed off data migration report;  
•  Post implementation review;  
•  Agreed plan for roll-out of turnkey systems to all APB branches; 
and  
•  Systems fully operational bank-wide in APB. 
Implementation of Major Activities:  •  Pre-bidding activities for turnkey contract: months 1 to 3; 
Number of months from grant  •  Bidding and contracting: months 3 to 8 
activities  •  Turnkey  contract  implementation,  supervision  and  quality 
assurance: months 9 to 14 
•  Roll-out of systems to all branches: months 15 to 24 

